c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Framer and Uizard share a solid foundation of core features including Templates, Drag And Drop, Brand Kit, Ai Generation. Where Framer pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Animations and Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Uizard uniquely offers Stock Assets, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Framer holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 7/10, while Uizard scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
d:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Framer and Uizard offer flexible pricing models. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Framer's free tier and Uizard's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
