10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Framer is best suited for designers, startups, portfolio sites, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Uizard, meanwhile, shines for product managers, non designers, rapid prototyping, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2013, Framer describes itself as \"AI-powered website builder with professional design and CMS capabilities.\" Uizard, established in 2018, positions itself as \"AI-powered UI design tool that turns ideas into interactive prototypes.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Framer** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (9 vs 8), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Uizard is a poor choice — far from it. Uizard excels in its own right, particularly for product managers and non designers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value beautiful design-first website builder, go with Framer. If generate ui from text descriptions matters more to you, Uizard is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
